- 1.0.3 | Mar 07 2026:
  [Fix] _alert_slack_post_message channel injection replaced sed s/// with
      awk to prevent crash when ALERT_SLACK_CHANNEL contains forward slash
      and data corruption when it contains ampersand; awk -v avoids both
      delimiter collision and backreference substitution
  [Fix] _alert_digest_flush now captures subshell exit code after flock
      timeout and propagates failure to caller; previously returned 0 on
      lock timeout, silently discarding the flush failure
  [Change] _alert_build_mime MIME boundary uses /dev/urandom-derived random
      suffix instead of $$ (PID) for improved uniqueness; falls back to
      PID if /dev/urandom is unavailable
  [Change] Removed redundant ${ALERT_TMPDIR:-/tmp} fallback in
      _alert_email_local text-via-sendmail path; ALERT_TMPDIR is always
      set at global scope, consistent with all other mktemp calls
  [Change] Added docstring to _alert_deliver_email documenting that the
      relay path always sends multipart/alternative regardless of format
      parameter (format only affects local MTA path)
